---
<section class="origin" id="origin">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="origin__inner reveal">
      <p class="overline">The Origin</p>
      <hr class="fire-rule" />
      <h2 class="display origin__heading">
        Built for<br/><em>something bigger.</em>
      </h2>
      <div class="origin__body">
        <p>
          In 2003, I raised my right hand and committed to something larger than myself. I became an 
          Airman of the United States Air Force — and from the moment I walked into service, I was 
          determined to be exceptional at it.
        </p>
        <p>
          I trained as a <strong>Mission Crew Commander</strong>, one of the most demanding intelligence 
          and electronic warfare roles in the Air Force. My aircraft was the <strong>EC-130H Compass Call</strong> — 
          a highly classified Electronic Attack platform so specialized that only a handful of 
          people in the world ever fly aboard it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Onboard, I was the Chief. I supervised a crew of nine, led mission planning, 
          and was accountable for every decision from wheels-up to wheels-down.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.origin {
  padding-block: var(--section-pad);
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--ash) 0%, var(--coal) 100%);
}
.origin__inner {
  max-width: 680px;
}
.origin__heading {
  font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
  color: var(--white);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
}
.origin__heading em {
  color: var(--amber);
  font-style: italic;
}
.origin__body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--bone);
  opacity: 0.85;
}
.origin__body strong {
  color: var(--amber);
  font-weight: 500;
}
</style>
